              "id": "Tm90ZVR3ZWV0OjIwNjk2NzUxNDMwNzc0NDk3Mjg=",
              "text": "I feel proud and happy to see water trucks going out every day to reach displaced families in Gaza. Today was truck #2, carrying 6,000 liters of clean water to an area facing severe shortages.\n\nPeople here are in urgent need of water, and the situation is getting harder every day. Many large organizations have stopped delivering water, increasing the suffering of families in the camps.\n\nThese families live in extremely dangerous areas and risk their lives every day, yet access to clean water remains very difficult. The need is enormous, and thousands of families are still waiting for these supplies.\n\nWe will continue this work as long as we can. A water truck will go out every day, God willing, because water is not a luxury it is a human right."
            }
